            <title>[TIKA-36] A convenience method for getting a document&apos;s content&apos;s text would be helpful.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-36</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, to get a parsed document&apos;s content value (e.g. title), one must do something like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        Content content = getContent(name);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        return content != null&lt;br/&gt;
                ? content.getValue()&lt;br/&gt;
                : null;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d like to suggest we create a method that does that in one place, so that users do not need to do that themselves.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch coming momentarily...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
